762
00:50:51.634 --> 00:50:54.834
decades, but two, because there were hints in the literature that it might actually

763
00:50:54.854 --> 00:50:57.994
play a functional role in cell signaling.

764
00:50:58.054 --> 00:51:01.474
And so a lot of the data is very difficult to mine in terms of having

765
00:51:01.494 --> 00:51:04.634
CA19-9 levels and prognoses, but in this recent study,

766
00:51:05.474 --> 00:51:07.774
a couple of years ago, they had really good metadata.

767
00:51:08.143 --> 00:51:11.794
And what I was able to do is actually take a look at very small tumors, so

768
00:51:12.294 --> 00:51:16.074
stage one, node-negative resections, and show that

769
00:51:16.134 --> 00:51:19.914
even in this context, with the exact same tumor sizes, all

