780
00:51:56.114 --> 00:51:59.274
The enzyme responsible for the final sialylation step,

781
00:51:59.334 --> 00:52:02.054
fucosyltransferase 3, is a pseudogene in all rodents.

782
00:52:02.094 --> 00:52:06.014
And so right away, that tells you that CA19-9 is not necessary for pancreatic tumor

783
00:52:06.034 --> 00:52:09.544
genesis. But I wanted to see if it played any sort of role in

784
00:52:09.574 --> 00:52:13.384
accelerating it. And so I figured out how to make CA19-9 in mice, and I

785
00:52:13.414 --> 00:52:16.844
created a series of mouse models that enabled me to induce CA19-9

786
00:52:16.894 --> 00:52:20.614
elevation, either just in the mouse pancreas, bile duct, and duodenum, or in the

787
00:52:20.654 --> 00:52:23.974
whole body of a mouse. And right away, you might wonder, does that cause just a

788
00:52:24.014 --> 00:52:27.174
massive autoimmune reaction? And the quick answer is no.

789
00:52:27.614 --> 00:52:30.754
We've studied this a lot because, in the beginning, we thought this could be an

790
00:52:30.794 --> 00:52:32.814
artifact instead of cool biology.

791
00:52:32.834 --> 00:52:35.454
And so I'm happy to take you through all that data offline.

792
00:52:35.474 --> 00:52:39.144
But most importantly is that when we turn it on in the entire body of the mouse,

793
00:52:39.294 --> 00:52:42.354
we only see signs of inflammation in the pancreas.

794
00:52:42.364 --> 00:52:45.734
And so that, to us, tells us there's something very specific about the importance

795
00:52:45.754 --> 00:52:47.694
of CA19-9 to pancreatic biology.

796
00:52:48.894 --> 00:52:52.844
And when we turn on CA19-9, the mice rapidly develop pancreatitis, and if

797
00:52:52.954 --> 00:52:56.054
you turn it on in the presence of a KRAS mutation, you can see within two weeks,

798
00:52:56.154 --> 00:52:59.554
the mice get high-grade PanINs, they get invasive

799
00:52:59.654 --> 00:53:03.574
carcinoma, and you can see CA19-9 is elevated in the ductal

800
00:53:03.584 --> 00:53:05.314
epithelium, which is what you would expect.

801
00:53:06.334 --> 00:53:10.194
This translates to a substantial decrease in survival in these

802
00:53:10.233 --> 00:53:13.744
mice. And so these mice, relative to CA19-9

803
00:53:13.744 --> 00:53:17.094
negative controls, so they do not have the CA19-9 alleles at

804
00:53:17.154 --> 00:53:21.123
all, or in the mice that have inducible CA19-9 but

805
00:53:21.134 --> 00:53:24.914
were not treated with DOX, versus those in which we added DOX to their

806
00:53:24.974 --> 00:53:28.294
drinking water. You can see that when we turn on CA19-9, we have

807
00:53:28.374 --> 00:53:31.734
survival, which is about as powerful as mutating

808
00:53:31.754 --> 00:53:35.114
p53. And so we weren't entirely surprised because

809
00:53:35.134 --> 00:53:37.994
pancreatitis does accelerate tumor genesis.

810
00:53:38.394 --> 00:53:42.274
But when I started my lab, I really wanted to understand, are these direct impacts

811
00:53:42.334 --> 00:53:44.374
to cell signaling and paracrine interactions?

812
00:53:44.894 --> 00:53:48.604
Or is there something that we're perhaps overestimating

813
00:53:48.634 --> 00:53:52.454
here? And so what we found is that when you're trying to learn how to bake a

814
00:53:52.514 --> 00:53:56.214
cake, if you just study the finished product, it's very difficult to understand how

815
00:53:56.254 --> 00:53:59.654
that cake came to be. So we need to watch somebody actually on a cooking show,

816
00:53:59.874 --> 00:54:03.404
right? And so we only turned on CA19-9 for a few days so we could

817
00:54:03.434 --> 00:54:07.334
take a step back and see what are the ingredients, what order

818
00:54:07.434 --> 00:54:10.104
do they get recruited to the pancreatic tumor microenvironment?

819
00:54:10.444 --> 00:54:13.754
And what we found is that three days of CA19-9 is sufficient to

820
00:54:13.794 --> 00:54:17.274
dramatically expand the fibroblast population and ramp up

821
00:54:17.314 --> 00:54:19.054
proliferation in that compartment.

822
00:54:19.574 --> 00:54:22.834
But at the same time, we're not just turning on CA19-9.

823
00:54:22.894 --> 00:54:26.314
We are remodeling the glycome. We are driving the production of different precursor

824
00:54:26.334 --> 00:54:30.104
molecules. We're decreasing the levels of available substrates for other types of

825
00:54:30.114 --> 00:54:32.623
