00:56:32.602 --> 00:56:34.102
as well as in Rolf Brekken's lab.

860
00:56:34.902 --> 00:56:38.342
And so we took a look and we saw indeed, there's a dramatic

861
00:56:38.382 --> 00:56:42.302
expansion of these antigen-presenting CAFs, as well as an increase in

862
00:56:42.381 --> 00:56:46.082
Treg differentiation, both by single-cell flow cytometry and

863
00:56:46.142 --> 00:56:50.122
immunohistochemistry. And so we wanted to take a closer look about how all

864
00:56:50.142 --> 00:56:53.842
this is happening, and so Rolf Brekken kindly provided these pancreatic

865
00:56:53.862 --> 00:56:57.722
mesothelial cells, which are the primary source of antigen-presenting

866
00:56:57.782 --> 00:57:01.682
fibroblasts in the pancreas. And we either treated them CA19-9 positive or

867
00:57:01.742 --> 00:57:05.722
CA19-9 negative condition media from these pancreatic organoids, or

868
00:57:05.762 --> 00:57:08.982
we did an antibody blocking experiment and measured the apCAF

869
00:57:08.992 --> 00:57:12.722
differentiation. And so what we can see is that CA19-9

870
00:57:12.842 --> 00:57:16.462
positive condition media can induce antigen-presenting CAF differentiation to

871
00:57:17.262 --> 00:57:20.382
a greater extent than its CA19-9 negative counterpart.

872
00:57:20.422 --> 00:57:24.202
And if we block CA19-9, we actually dramatically change the secreted

873
00:57:24.402 --> 00:57:27.922
cytokines and secreted factors, and this leads to a

874
00:57:27.942 --> 00:57:31.902
dramatic impairment in antigen-presenting

875
00:57:32.082 --> 00:57:36.042
CAF differentiation. And if we take a look at our

876
00:57:36.382 --> 00:57:38.602
antibody blockade experiment in vivo, you can

877
00:57:39.462 --> 00:57:43.182
then again see that the antigen presenting into your differentiation decreases,

878
00:57:43.322 --> 00:57:46.842
showing that this is a specific impact of CA19-9.

879
00:57:47.762 --> 00:57:51.082
And so what we wanted to understand next is

880
00:57:51.142 --> 00:57:54.482
basically what is driving these signals.

881
00:57:54.662 --> 00:57:58.312
And CA19-9 elevation, as I mentioned, it's going to modify many

882
00:57:58.362 --> 00:58:01.402
different things. A lot of those things are going to be quite subtle.

883
00:58:01.422 --> 00:58:05.222
And so is there one possible mechanism that we could use to get a paper

