910
00:59:38.162 --> 00:59:41.582
for this cascade, but I'm not going to show you that data today.

911
00:59:42.602 --> 00:59:46.462
And so this is a cascade that's initiated by

912
00:59:46.502 --> 00:59:48.842
CA19-9, but really hyped up

913
00:59:50.342 --> 00:59:53.762
ILIN alpha and TGF beta expression. But what's the intermediary, right?

914
00:59:53.802 --> 00:59:56.212
What's the CA19-9 modified protein that's doing this?

915
00:59:56.572 --> 01:00:00.492
And so we went back to the original work where perhaps one of the best ones

916
01:00:00.522 --> 01:00:04.082
that we've characterized so far is this secreted glycoprotein called fibulin 3,

917
01:00:04.122 --> 01:00:07.042
which has many different EGF-like domains.

918
01:00:07.062 --> 01:00:11.002
And we showed that this is CA19-9 modified, and when it is, it can co-precipitate

919
01:00:11.022 --> 01:00:14.622
with EGF receptor to a greater extent and lead to hyperactivation of EGF

920
01:00:14.642 --> 01:00:18.462
receptor, both in pancreatitis and now also we've shown in pancreatic cancer

921
01:00:18.522 --> 01:00:22.122
organoids, where you see that when we turn on CA19-9, we get increased

922
01:00:22.142 --> 01:00:25.422
