923
01:00:25.462 --> 01:00:29.178
disappears.Now, APCAFs do not express EGF

924
01:00:29.218 --> 01:00:31.758
receptor. Other types of CAFs certainly do.

925
01:00:31.818 --> 01:00:35.718
But what we have seen is that EGF receptor signaling in other cell

926
01:00:35.778 --> 01:00:38.488
systems can drive IL-1alpha and TGF-beta production.

927
01:00:38.898 --> 01:00:42.808
And so on a whim, Heman was working on fibulin 3, Jasper was working on

928
01:00:42.838 --> 01:00:46.778
the TME. I was like, "Are these actually the same project?" And it turned

929
01:00:46.818 --> 01:00:50.538
out that it was. And when we knocked down fibulin 3, now we had a substantial

930
01:00:50.598 --> 01:00:54.358
reduction in IL-1alpha and TGF-beta in both mouse and human organoids.

931
01:00:54.678 --> 01:00:58.518
And so this to us said that this is a fibulin 3 mediated EGF receptor

932
01:00:58.578 --> 01:01:02.458
dependent process, which we've also now shown both in vitro and in vivo

933
01:01:02.538 --> 01:01:04.958
using pan-ERBB kinase inhibitors.

934
01:01:07.498 --> 01:01:11.298
What did this do to APCAF differentiation in the in vitro differentiation

935
01:01:11.358 --> 01:01:15.298
model? The fibulin 3 knocked down organoids, even in the CA19-9 positive

936
01:01:15.378 --> 01:01:18.518
setting, lose their ability to induce antigen-presenting CAF

937
01:01:18.528 --> 01:01:21.838
differentiation. But when I was trying to sell the in vivo

938
01:01:21.898 --> 01:01:25.558
investigation of this final piece of the puzzle to my

939
01:01:25.578 --> 01:01:26.118
students,

940
01:01:27.678 --> 01:01:31.418
I'm an organoid person, but transplanting these organoids, it takes about 6 to

941
01:01:31.478 --> 01:01:35.158
12 months for them to form tumors. And so they would like to graduate this year.

942
01:01:35.238 --> 01:01:39.118
So I told them that they could use 2D cells, which if Dave is in here in the

943
01:01:39.178 --> 01:01:42.498
audience, I'm sorry. It's quite blasphemous. But we used 2D cells.

944
01:01:42.898 --> 01:01:46.068
We set up the same system. We knocked down fibulin 3 in the CA19-9 positive

945
01:01:46.138 --> 01:01:48.698
setting. This has no impact on their in vitro

946
01:01:50.678 --> 01:01:54.648
proliferation, but you can again see that it leads to a reduction in

947
01:01:54.648 --> 01:01:56.578
IL-1alpha and TGF-beta production.

948
01:01:57.138 --> 01:02:00.778
And so what we wanted to do is look at in vivo tumor formation.

949
01:02:00.878 --> 01:02:04.298
You can see in two different independent cell lines that you have a

950
01:02:04.318 --> 01:02:07.838
remarkable decrease in tumor growth in both the

951
01:02:07.878 --> 01:02:10.698
volume over time as well as the endpoint.

952
01:02:11.058 --> 01:02:14.838
And when we port the system over to NSG mice, we completely lose any

953
01:02:15.298 --> 01:02:18.598
tumor size differences, suggesting to us that this is really immune

954
01:02:18.658 --> 01:02:19.318
mediated.

955
01:02:20.218 --> 01:02:23.218
And so what we wanted to, again, do is see, well, what

956
01:02:23.858 --> 01:02:25.458
happens to the tumor microenvironment?

957
01:02:25.518 --> 01:02:28.258
Do we reverse this immunosuppressive remodeling?

958
01:02:28.618 --> 01:02:31.498
And what we find is that when you're looking for antigen-presenting CAFs, you have

959
01:02:31.538 --> 01:02:35.117
to find the CAFs that are CD45 negative, but MHC positive.

960
01:02:35.378 --> 01:02:37.838
And we see a dramatic reduction in those fibroblasts.

961
01:02:37.858 --> 01:02:41.458
But importantly to the CAF field, I think it's important to note that we still see

962
01:02:41.498 --> 01:02:44.518
plenty of myCAFs and we still see some iCAFs.

963
01:02:45.358 --> 01:02:49.118
When we look at Tregs, Treg infiltration is usually an early event

964
01:02:49.258 --> 01:02:52.598
in pancreas tumor genesis. But

965
01:02:53.258 --> 01:02:55.838
what they essentially do is suppress the immune system.

966
01:02:55.878 --> 01:02:58.438
And so we look at our CD8 T cells instead.

967
01:02:58.518 --> 01:03:02.437
At endpoint, we can see a dramatic expansion in CD8 T cells.

968
01:03:02.818 --> 01:03:06.448
And so I think that what we've done is kind of uncovered this really

969
01:03:06.478 --> 01:03:10.458
interesting TME remodeling axis where CA19-9 kind of triggers

970
01:03:10.518 --> 01:03:14.178
multiple different cascades. So certainly activating EGF receptor

971
01:03:15.218 --> 01:03:18.638
in the ductal cell compartment is going to be pro-survival,

972
01:03:18.778 --> 01:03:22.258
pro-growth. But at the same time, this is going to lead to remodeling

973
01:03:22.778 --> 01:03:26.158
of the different immunomodulatory factors that these cancer cells can

974
01:03:26.218 --> 01:03:30.078
secrete. And so I'm not saying that in the absence of CA19-9, this axis

975
01:03:30.138 --> 01:03:33.898
isn't active, just that in a CA19-9 high tumor, which is about

976
01:03:33.938 --> 01:03:37.658
90% of pancreas cancers, you're going to have much more

977
01:03:37.718 --> 01:03:41.578
immunosuppressive TME remodeling than we are ever going to have

978
01:03:41.618 --> 01:03:45.538
happen in our mice. And this increased production of IL-1alpha

979
01:03:45.548 --> 01:03:49.478
and TGF-beta is going to induce APCAF differentiation, CD4 T

980
01:03:49.538 --> 01:03:53.438
cell differentiation to Tregs, and inhibition of our CD8 T cells.

981
01:03:53.788 --> 01:03:55.638
And so I think that this is something where

982
01:03:57.198 --> 01:04:00.158
sometimes the mouse models can overestimate response.

983
01:04:00.178 --> 01:04:04.098
Well, maybe that's because they lack some of these human glycan derived

984
01:04:04.218 --> 01:04:04.738
axes.

985
01:04:05.678 --> 01:04:09.278
And so I think this is really early days in terms of fully understanding everything

986
01:04:09.318 --> 01:04:12.608
that CA19-9 does. And I'll be the first one to admit that

987
01:04:12.658 --> 01:04:15.478
glycosylation is complex and difficult to study.

988
01:04:15.918 --> 01:04:19.718
I'm lucky in that CA19-9 is really driven by the action of a single

989
01:04:19.898 --> 01:04:23.778
enzyme, whereas in many of these other cases, you're talking about a network that

990
01:04:23.818 --> 01:04:27.598
is dozens of enzymes. But I think this is a really good example where

991
01:04:27.758 --> 01:04:30.878
taking a step back and understanding the biomarkers that we've used for

992
01:04:30.938 --> 01:04:34.838
cancers for almost five decades now

993
01:04:34.878 --> 01:04:38.648
might actually be functional. And in this case, I've shown that CA19-9

994
01:04:38.678 --> 01:04:41.938
elevation triggers this immunosuppressive TME remodeling.

995
01:04:41.958 --> 01:04:45.718
But there are hundreds of other CA19-9 modified proteins,

996
01:04:46.058 --> 01:04:48.678
and they all change their function in slightly different ways.

997
01:04:48.978 --> 01:04:52.518
And so for fibulin 3, how does this glycosylation actually

998
01:04:52.528 --> 01:04:55.138
increase its binding to EGF receptor?

999
01:04:55.198 --> 01:04:57.918
For the RAS therapeutics

1000
01:04:58.938 --> 01:05:02.918
interest in the field, we are seeing how this intersects with RAS

1001
01:05:02.958 --> 01:05:06.658
inhibitor response, as well as the obvious next step is to

1002
01:05:06.718 --> 01:05:10.358
combine CA19-9 blockade or blockade of this access with immune

1003
01:05:10.438 --> 01:05:14.398
checkpoint blockade, and then really going after the massive repertoire of

1004
01:05:14.438 --> 01:05:18.338
CA19-9 modified proteins and other glycan changes that occur

1005
01:05:18.358 --> 01:05:20.128
during pancreatic tumor genesis.

1006
01:05:21.678 --> 01:05:25.578
And so none of this work could be possible without a big team.

1007
01:05:25.638 --> 01:05:29.618
And so this is, again, this was work led by Heman and Jasper,

1008
01:05:29.658 --> 01:05:31.688
who are both finishing up their PhDs.

1009
01:05:31.958 --> 01:05:35.848
But we have a large support network of technicians as well as friends in the

1010
01:05:35.918 --> 01:05:39.298
lab that everybody kind of helps when you have a big in vivo study.

1011
01:05:39.378 --> 01:05:42.508
But also if any of you run an organoid program, it does require a lot of

