01:23:59.506 --> 01:24:03.386
But is there an opportunity to do something in terms of preventing this

1319
01:24:03.426 --> 01:24:05.666
disease in terms of those who are at high risk?

1320
01:24:06.186 --> 01:24:09.506
And so I promised some of my friends in the audience I would use

1321
01:24:10.306 --> 01:24:13.386
the word cleanse in my talk, and here it is.

1322
01:24:13.446 --> 01:24:16.366
So we came up with this concept of KRAS cleanse.

1323
01:24:16.836 --> 01:24:19.786
So you have oral KRAS inhibitors, not the ones we have now.

1324
01:24:20.126 --> 01:24:23.506
I think they're still too toxic, but it's getting better.

1325
01:24:24.006 --> 01:24:26.166
Even in the cancer context, they're getting better.

1326
01:24:26.726 --> 01:24:29.006
So a little bit of provocative idea.

1327
01:24:29.446 --> 01:24:33.166
Oral KRAS inhibitors for a few weeks in these high-risk individuals above a

1328
01:24:33.206 --> 01:24:33.886
certain age.

1329
01:24:34.826 --> 01:24:38.236
You take it for a few weeks, you cleanse all the KRAS from your

1330
01:24:38.246 --> 01:24:41.806
body. You come back next year, you get another KRAS cleanse.

1331
01:24:41.826 --> 01:24:45.546
Maybe add vaccines annually as a booster to sustain the immune response.

1332
01:24:45.806 --> 01:24:49.746
Pipe dream, but so was drugging KRAS 10 years

1333
01:24:49.806 --> 01:24:52.426
